<p>I am creating a website using Django and I have two views that both use Django forms.  The first view uses a form that allows the user to specify a data range and then click submit.  On submit, the values from the first view are then given to the second view.  I use a Django form in the second view to create a textarea that the user is allowed to edit; when they are done editing the text field they click another submit button.  </p>  <p>However, I am having the problem that when the second view is rendered, the request object is already <code>POST</code> so my forms aren't loading properly.  Does anyone know how to fix this?</p>  <p><strong>views.py</strong></p>  <pre><code>def DateSelector(request):    initial_end = "2015/12"    search_vars = {}    if request.method == 'POST':     form_start    = TextFieldForm(request.POST,section_label="",initial_value=initial_start,required=True,prefix="WindowStart")     form_end      = TextFieldForm(request.POST,section_label="",initial_value=initial_end,required=True,prefix="windowEnd")              if form_start.is_valid():         WS_raw = form_start.cleaned_data['text']         try:             logger.debug("Window Start time: %s" % WS_raw)             search_vars.update({'WINDOW_START': str(WS_raw)})         except:             logger.error("The start date you entered is incorrectly formatted.")             return render(request,'InterfaceApp/error.html',message)     else:         logger.error("The start date you entered is incorrectly formatted.")      if form_end.is_valid():         WE = form_end.cleaned_data['text']         try:             logger.debug("Window End time: %s" % WE)             search_vars.update({'WINDOW_END': str(WE)})         except:             logger.error("The end date you entered is incorrectly formatted.")     else:         logger.error("The end date you entered is incorrectly formatted.")      return USNEmailer(request,search_vars)    else:     form_start    = TextFieldForm(section_label="",ini